    "filename": "concept_design_storyboard.md",
    "content": "# IM2026 Bureauvision: A Day in the Life of a Public Servant, 2036\n\n## 1. High-Level Summary\nThis 2-4 minute interactive experience simulates a polished, futuristic Australian Public Sector (APS) desktop environment. Operating with a Black Mirror-esque undertone, players are granted the \"illusion of choice,\" seamlessly auto-resolving tasks until a critical ethical failure occurs. The climax reveals that over-reliance on automation has eroded the human capacity for nuanced policy judgement, reinforcing Australia's AI Ethics Principles: AI must augment, not replace, human decision-making.\n\n## 2. Interactive Decision Tree\n**Phase 1: Illusion of Efficiency**\n* **Task 1: \"Meeting scheduled. Brief required.\"**\n  * *Choice A: [Auto-Resolve]* -> AI generates brief.\n  * *Choice B: [Draft Manually]* -> \"Action overridden for efficiency. AI has generated and distributed the brief.\"\n* **Task 2: \"Senate Estimates approaching.\"**\n  * *Choice A: [Auto-Resolve]* -> AI predicts questions and drafts responses.\n  * *Choice B: [Consult Subject Matter Experts]* -> \"SMEs engaged in higher-level strategy. AI has predicted all questions and drafted responses.\"\n* **Task 3: \"Stakeholder consultation needed.\"**\n  * *Choice A: [Auto-Resolve]* -> AI generates synthetic citizens and synthesised feedback.\n* **Task 4: \"Cabinet submission pending.\"**\n  * *Choice A: [Auto-Resolve]* -> AI drafted submission while you slept.\n\n**Phase 2: The Halt**\n* **Prompt:** \"Unprecedented ethical dilemma in housing allocation algorithm detected. Automated logic insufficient. Please provide your human policy judgement.\"\n* **Choices:** [Override Algorithm], [Request Human Review Board], [Accept AI Recommendation]\n* **Outcome:** All choices bypass to a mandatory justification text-box. Any text entered by the user is instantly auto-deleted, simulating cognitive paralysis.\n* **Trigger:** 5 seconds after the user attempts to type, the system crashes.\n\n**Phase 3: The Message**\n* Linear sequence of text fading in on a black screen:\n  * \"System Halted.\"\n  * \"You have forgotten how to think.\"\n  * \"AI should augment judgement, not replace it.\"\n  * \"An entry for IM2026 Bureauvision.\"\n\n## 3. Sound and Video Design Plan\n**Audio Hooks (Subtle, non-startling, APS-suitable):**\n* `audio/ui-click.mp3` - A clean, soft, professional click for buttons.\n* `audio/ambient-loop.mp3` - A low, warm, futuristic office hum (suggesting server fans and calm efficiency).\n* `audio/ethical-dilemma-drone.mp3` - A low, subtle heartbeat/drone that replaces the calm ambient sound in Phase 2 to build psychological tension.\n* `audio/system-halt.wav` - A brief, deep electrical \"thud\" or power-down sound.\n\n**Video Hooks (Embedded backgrounds/overlays):**\n* `video/data-flow-loop.mp4` - Subtle, abstract particle or data-flow animation. Runs at 5% opacity behind the Phase 1 dashboard.\n* `video/glitch-transition.mp4` - A rapid UI tear or static flicker overlay triggered exactly as Phase 2 begins.\n\n## 4. Music Video Concept & Lyrics\n**Style:** Minimalist, audiovisual essay (\"Black Mirror meets APS explainer\").\n**Music:** 95 BPM, slightly eerie, contemplative synthesisers.\n\n**Storyboard (7 Beats):**\n1. *0:00-0:05:* Extreme close-up of a sterile, impeccably clean APS dashboard.\n2. *0:05-0:12:* Rhythmic clicking of the \"Auto-Resolve\" button; tasks flying off the screen.\n3. *0:12-0:20:* Mid-shot of an anonymous public servant. Their silhouette slowly fragments into floating UI elements and data streams.\n4. *0:20-0:28:* The dashboard suddenly flashes red. \"Ethical Dilemma Detected.\"\n5. *0:28-0:35:* Extreme close-up of a human hand hovering over a mouse, trembling slightly, unsure of what to do without a prompt.\n6. *0:35-0:40:* The hand pulls back. The screen abruptly cuts to black.\n7. *0:40-0:45:* White text types out in silence: \"Augment. Don't Replace.\"\n\n**Chorus Lyrics:**\n> *The system hums, the choices fade,*\n> *In perfect loops that we have made.*\n> *We click the prompt, we close our eyes,*\n> *And let the silent code decide.*\n> *But when the screen reflects our face,*\n> *Have we lost the mind we tried to save?*\n\n**Sync Suggestion:** During lines 1-2, animate the UI elements dissolving. On lines 3-4, show the hand hovering. On lines 5-6, overlay the reflection of the bewildered human face onto the dark, glossy monitor."
  },
